Sausage Mushroom Pasta

While preparing other ingredients, bring a pot of salted water to a boil and keep at a bare simmer.
Also, warm up a cast iron pan over low heat.

- 2 medium shallots
- 2 cloves garlic
- 2 Tbsp dried parsley
Finely mince shallots and garlic. Separate out 1/4 of each. Separate out 1/2 of the parsley

- 6 oz parmigiano-reggiano cheese
Grate cheese, and separate out 1/3.

- 8 oz sweet italian sausage (or other type)
- 1 lb mushrooms (any type, or a mix of types)
Remove any casings from sausage, and thinly slice mushrooms.

- 1 cup panko breadcrumbs
- 2 Tbsp olive oil
+ 1/2 of the parsley
+ 1/3 of the cheese
+ 1/4 of the garlic and shallots
+ salt
+ pepper
Toss together in a medium bowl.  Season with salt and pepper.

- 3 Tbsp butter
Melt butter in cast iron over medium-high heat until foaming.
Add sausage and cook until well browned, about 7 minutes.
Break up sausage with a masher or spoon as it cooks.

Remove sausage from pan with a slotted spoon and reserve, leaving fat in pan.
Add mushrooms to pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until moisture has boiled off and mushrooms are brown, about 10 minutes.

- 1lb box rotini or similar
Meanwhile, return water to boiling, and cook pasta about a minute less than "al dente".
When done, drain and reserve pasta.

- 1 Tbsp lemon juice
- 1 Tbsp soy sauce
+ remaining garlic and shallots
Add garlic and shallots to the mushrooms.
Cook just until fragrant, about 30 seconds, then immediately add lemon juice and soy sauce.

- 2.5 Tbsp flour
- 2 cups chicken broth
- 1 cup heavy cream
Add flour and cook, stirring, until a film/coating forms on the pan and on the mushrooms.
Add broth, a little at a time, stirring to fully combine before adding more.
Add cream and stir to combine.
Bring to a light boil and cook for about 2 minutes until thickened.

+ remaining cheese and parsley
+ sausage
Stir in cheese and parsley until cheese is melted.
Stir in sausage
Put rack about 10 inches under broiler and preheat broiler to high

+ 1/2 the pasta
+ breadcrumb mixture
Stir half the pasta into mushroom mixture (the other half is not used)
Top with breadcrumbs.
Broil until just golden brown, being careful not to burn, about 2-3 minutes.
